This paper discusses the use of formal methods for software verification, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on the use of refinement types, which are a type of static type system, indicating a possible fit with programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The application of the tool to cognitive neuroscience suggests a potential fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
